Have been a customer since the late 70's love their combo's, and they always have freshly made fries. Now they know how to satisfy your tummy.

I recently gone into this so called "family business" and let me tell you, the service I have received was not pleasant. For one, they don't acknowledge you when you come into their restaurant (not even a "hi, I will be right with you"). Secondly, the most important thing is they don't wear gloves, doesn't matter how many times you washed your hands, it's common sense when handling food, you should always always wear gloves. Lastly, they dont accept debit or credit. I avoid coming to this restaurant as much as possible. As should everyone else. There are better restaurants on Taylor that have a more pleasant vibe.

I have been coming here since I was a kid. I live in Michigan and every time I come here, I buy several sandwiches to take home and freeze. Tradition and its best! Service is always quick and awesome and food rocks! I refuse to buy an Italian beef sandwich from anywhere else.

We ordered Chicago style hot dogs but we did not receive Chicago style hot dogs because they were missing key ingredients,   I would much preferred if they had just told us they did not serve a Chicago style hot dog.  We had traveled a long way for our disappointment.

I love Patio fries but for some reason this day they were very undercook, also I ordered gravy bread and they were buy one get one free, well I see why because the bread was very old. Although I asked for my my gravy bread to be extra dip with they did because I witness it the bread was still dry and old tasting. Patio has fell off a lot from back in the days
Still is the place to get Good Beefs and fries. And if you haven't had a Potato sandwich from them, you are so Sleep. The Bomb

This place is simply a hidden legend in Chicago. From what I unserstand its been a monument in the neighbirhood for years.. I'm an out of towner who was suggested to this place by my uber driver who grew up in the neighborhood. I will go back. I walked in and asked what they were famous for and they all shouted without hesitation a sausage/steak sandwich. Dipped. Wasnt even sure what it meant but said yes. First bite I was wearing it on my shirt. Damn good. This place gives me a reason to stay at the local medical district Marriott again.

Update: Returned food and owner wouldn't give me a refund. They only take cash and now I know why. Probably to many charge back. Offered me a gift card for four sandwiches out of 8. Never again will I go there.  This place is not the same! I'm a long time customer (was my mom's favorite place, so started going here as a kid). My favorite is the Italian beef dipped with gardenia peppers. First off the got order wrong and added sweet peppers. Staff normally friendly but not last night maybe they was tired from a long night.  The most important aspect of this visit was the sandwiches SUCKED! ordered 8 Italian beefs and they were all wrong. The bread was dry and tough (I asked for them to be dipped a couple times to be wet and juicy). All had sweet peppers. Also their juice that they dipped sandwiches in has changed and taste bland. Tamale boats were dried out with an old tamale and old chili. Best part of visit is that we also got a couple of hotdogs and they are still Vienna Beef hot dogs and tasted good (the reason I have them 3 stars instead of 2). Let's get it together Patios! You can do better! Will be bringing beers back today. Feeling Disappointed.

If you are hungry for the best chili dogs Italian beef and several other Chicago style sandwiches and sides this the place to visit. The restaurant is always clean as a hospital lab. The service goes beyond expectations. They offer a variety of party and special event packages that are priced reasonably.  Attend!!!!

Normally Patio is just an ok place to eat but on today, 2/13/13 the experience was horrible.  The employees do not was their hands.  I pointed this out and the response was inappropriate, rude, and argumentive.  They do not care about sanitation in this place.  They use the same towels to wipe down tables and equipment for their hands. There is no visible sink.  There was also a cockroach on the wall.  So in my mind, they do not care about their customers only the money.  I reported this establishment to the Health Department.  I do not recommend unless you want illness.  Dirty hands YUK!!!
